{
  "texts": [
    "They declare a fast and clothe themselves in sackcloth, fervently seeking divine mercy.",
    "News of the city's repentance reaches the ears of the king, who, moved by the genuine remorse of his people, joins them in their acts of repentance.",
    "He issues a decree, urging every living creature within the city to join in the fervent plea for forgiveness.",
    "Word spreads throughout the land, reaching the ears of neighboring nations.",
    "Astonished by the spiritual transformation unfolding in Nineveh, they too are compelled to seek the Lord's mercy."
  ]
}